{DIALOGUE}: Let's go!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSEUP – GEORGE AND MARY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the MUSIC starts and couples begin dancing once more, they look at each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not very good at this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARY
{DIALOGUE}: Neither am I.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Okay – what can we lose?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start their Charleston.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see a SERIES OF SHOTS of various couples doing their routines, some good, some bad.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSEUP – FREDDIE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Leaning against the railing around the dance floor, looking daggers at George.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mickey, a young punk who has had one too many, is beside him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MICKEY
{DIALOGUE}: What's the matter, Othello – jealous?
{DIALOGUE}: Did you know there's a swimming pool under this floor?
{DIALOGUE}: And did you know that button behind you causes this floor to open up?
{DIALOGUE}: And did you further know that George Bailey is dancing right over that crack?
{DIALOGUE}: And I've got the key?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Freddie needs no more.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes the key from Mickey and turns the switch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The floor begins to part in the middle, each half sliding under the bleacher seats.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pandemonium starts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dancers begin to scream as they try to get off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Some are so engrossed in dancing they continue at top speed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Teachers and elders start to scurry off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the floor opens, it reveals an attractive, lighted swimming pool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and Mary are so busy dancing they don't notice the floor opening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spotlights concentrate on them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They mistake the screams for cheers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and Mary dancing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: They're cheering us.
{DIALOGUE}: We must be good.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd watching George and Mary dancing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They move backwards until finally they reach the edge of the floor and fall into the pool below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SERIES OF SHOTS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and Mary still trying to dance in the water – the crowd on the edge cheering them – some of the crowd leap into the pool – the principal trying to restore order, finally clasps his hands like a diver and leaps in himself.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
{META_DATA}: FADE IN:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. TREE-LINED RESIDENTIAL STREET – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and Mary.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The night is warm with a bright moon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George is dressed in jersey sweater and oversize football pants that keep wanting to come down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mary is in an old white bath robe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Each is carrying their wet clothes tied into a bundle that leaves a trail of dripping water.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they near the camera we hear them singing:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE AND MARY
{META_DATA}: (singing)
{DIALOGUE}: Buffalo Gals can't you come out tonight.
{DIALOGUE}: Can't you come out tonight.
{DIALOGUE}: Can't you come out tonight.
{DIALOGUE}: Buffalo Gals can't you come out tonight and dance by the light of the moon.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Hot dog!
{DIALOGUE}: Just like an organ.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARY
{DIALOGUE}: Beautiful.
