{META_DATA}: WIPE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NICK'S BAR – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is Martini's place, but almost unrecognizable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cheerful Italian feeling is gone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is now more of a hard-drinking joint, a honky-tonk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Same bar, tables have no covers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People are lower down and tougher.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nick the bartender is behind the bar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and Clarence come in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George does not notice the difference, but Clarence is all eyes and beaming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They go up to the bar.
