{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Merry Christmas, you wonderful old Building and Loan!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BANK – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George notices a light in Potter's office window, and races across the street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. POTTER'S OFFICE – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Potter is seated working at his desk, his goon by his side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George pounds on the window.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{META_DATA}: (from outside)
{DIALOGUE}: Merry Christmas, Mr. Potter!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George runs off as Potter looks up from his work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: POTTER
{DIALOGUE}: Happy New Year to you – in jail!
{DIALOGUE}: Go on home – they're waiting for you!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. GEORGE'S HOME – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lights are on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a fire in the fireplace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Christmas tree is fully decorated with presents stacked around.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ENTRANCE HALL – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carter, the bank examiner, a newspaper reporter and photographer, and a sheriff, are waiting in the hall for George.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George comes dashing in the front door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{META_DATA}: (excitedly)
{DIALOGUE}: Mary...
{META_DATA}: (sees the men)
{DIALOGUE}: Well, hello, Mr. Bank Examiner!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He grabs his hand and shakes it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARTER
{META_DATA}: (surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Bailey, there's a deficit!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{DIALOGUE}: Eight thousand dollars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SHERIFF
{META_DATA}: (reaching into pocket)
{DIALOGUE}: George, I've got a little paper here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{META_DATA}: (happily)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll bet it's a warrant for my arrest.
{DIALOGUE}: Isn't it wonderful?
{DIALOGUE}: Merry Christmas!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The photographer sets off a flash bulb.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Reporters?
{DIALOGUE}: Where's Mary?
{META_DATA}: (calling)
{DIALOGUE}: Mary!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George runs to the kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets no answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he goes:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, look at this wonderful old drafty house!
{DIALOGUE}: Mary!
{DIALOGUE}: Mary!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He comes running back to the hall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Have you seen my wife?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHILDREN'S VOICES
{DIALOGUE}: Merry Christmas, Daddy!
{DIALOGUE}: Merry Christmas, Daddy!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. STAIRS – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MEDIUM SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three children are at the top of the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are in their pajamas.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Kids!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George starts to run up the stairs, and the old familiar knob on the banister comes off in his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He kisses it lovingly and puts it back, then continues up the stairs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Pete – kids – Janie – Tommy.
{META_DATA}: (takes them in his arms)
{DIALOGUE}: I could eat you up!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. TOP OF STAIRS – NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLOSE SHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George and the kids.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is hugging them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Where's your mother?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANIE
{DIALOGUE}: She went looking for you with Uncle Billy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Zuzu comes running out of her bedroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: George crushes her to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ZUZU
{DIALOGUE}: Daddy!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GEORGE
{DIALOGUE}: Zuzu – Zuzu.
{DIALOGUE}: My little gingersnap!
{DIALOGUE}: How do you feel?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ZUZU
{DIALOGUE}: Fine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANIE
{DIALOGUE}: And not a smitch of temperature.
